      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is equivalent to the (to me, at least) much more readable:\n\n(a.has_value() \u003d\u003d b.has_value()) \u0026\u0026 (!a.has_value() || *a \u003d\u003d *b)\n\nSeems like it would be better to use straightforward expressions like this rather than nested ternaries.",
