      "writtenOn": "2021-06-22T19:22:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The structure of these comparators was actually patterned directly off of the C++17 spec:\nhttp://screen/8abZVagiFNkXgib\nhttp://screen/BWeft8zXURuAUKR\n\nAbseil\u0027s implementation also follows a similar pattern; I correctness-checked my work against theirs:\nhttp://screen/AsY33GoVyYPDUjJ\n\nI did take a few liberties with the \"optional x value\" forms, but I think there is some value here in keeping things in line with the standard since the checks are actually pretty nuanced.\n\nIf you want I can reformat them onto multiple lines? Might make the ternaries read better.\n\n  return a.has_value() !\u003d b.has_value() ? false :\n                         !a.has_value() ? true :\n                                          (*a \u003d\u003d *b);",
      "parentUuid": "600bcf24_968f1ff4",
